Where are we going?

25
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:12,774
Nowhere.

26
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:22,075
Glen, can I tempt you?
Thank you.

27
00:03:22,243 --> 00:03:25,454
I often take something snacky
to Nicholas this time of day.

28
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:28,457
I know how the brain needs feeding.
Mm.

29
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:31,752
So how you settling in?

30
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:32,961
Great.

31
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:37,257
The last writers' retreat I was at, I
kind of froze my balls off, you know?

32
00:03:37,425 --> 00:03:39,801
Screeching fire doors
and curried lasagna,

33
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:43,555
and a needy poet,
from whom I still bear the scars.

34
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:48,477
Well, we try to keep it peaceful here.
Far from the madding crowd.

35
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:50,145
May I?

36
00:03:50,313 --> 00:03:52,481
Well, it's paradise.

37
00:03:54,609 --> 00:03:57,945
In Ewedown?
What are you doing there?

38
00:03:58,112 --> 00:03:59,529
I haven't told her yet.

39
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:03,242
Why not? You keep saying
you want to be with me.

40
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:08,121
