83
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:07,342
Yeah.
We could walk up the garage.

84
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:10,846
I'm supposed to be helping
my mom up at Stonefield.

85
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:13,390
They keep you busy.
Yeah.

86
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:16,017
You never stop, you.

87
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:18,728
Bet them writers are wankers.

88
00:07:18,896 --> 00:07:20,856
It was called From Hearth to Heath:

89
00:07:21,023 --> 00:07:23,608
The Doomsday and Revelation
in Victorian Verse.

90
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:24,818
What was it about?

91
00:07:24,986 --> 00:07:29,156
Well, you know, pale poets on laudanum
and dark towers and sunless seas.

92
00:07:29,323 --> 00:07:31,324
A little "Sturm und Drang" in a teacup.

93
00:07:31,492 --> 00:07:32,534
Did it sell?

94
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:38,165
Well, of course, my kind of books aren't
about sales, that's not why I write. So, no.

95
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:42,294
So, what are you working on next?

96
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:43,795
Thomas Hardy.

97
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:47,132
Is there anything left to say
about that maudlin bore?

98
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,969
Excuse me, but there's nothing dull about Hardy.
That is a misconception.

99
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:54,931
At least you've been published.
I'm seething with envy.

100
00:07:55,099 --> 00:07:58,518
I'd love to be published.
I publish myself on the Internet.

101
00:07:58,686 --> 00:08:01,146
Do you earn money doing that?
No.

102
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:03,106
What do you write?
Lesbian crime.

103
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:07,903
I'm here picking up tips
from the master.

104
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:16,745
- Beth?
- Yeah?

105
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:19,039
Why don't I just pop out on my own?

106
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:21,249
Well, I'm ready now. Come on.

107
00:08:21,417 --> 00:08:23,043
Is that...?

108
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:25,420
I mean, are you wearing that?

109
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:31,343
It just looks a bit hot.

110
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:35,931
