It's just...

121
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:08,463
Beth, it's not anything.
Who is she?

122
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:11,216
So she's on her way in,
the bride and groom are...

123
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:14,135
Just a researcher on Radio 4.
What's her name?

124
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:16,888
Nadia. Nadia Patel.
Patel? She's in your book.

125
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:19,182
No. No. I met her when I was on
Desert Island Discs.

126
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:21,351
You put her in your book.
Well, just the name.

127
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:23,144
Desert Island Discs was a year ago.
Yes...

128
00:09:23,312 --> 00:09:24,354
So "once or twice"?

129
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:25,814
I was going to tell you.

130
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:27,816
In the book, from your woman.

131
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:29,818
Saying that they're coming
to the par...

132
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:33,154
I've had enough of this.
Beth. I'm a ruin, I know.

133
00:09:33,322 --> 00:09:35,574
But I've been in a real state
about this.

134
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:37,993
I didn't want to hurt you.

135
00:09:39,036 --> 00:09:40,870
How could you lie to my face?

136
00:09:41,038 --> 00:09:43,498
Can we talk calmly?
There are people out there.

137
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:45,333
You looked me in the face and lied.

138
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:47,544
For God's sake,
we're surrounded by novelists.

139
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:50,088
You bastard.
Beth,

140
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:53,091
we're like a pair of compasses.
Don't you dare.

141
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:55,093
Joined solidly at the top,

142
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:58,138
but with the ends
able to roam in freedom.

143
00:10:00,182 --> 00:10:02,475
That's her, isn't it?
Are you keeping her waiting?

144
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:04,519
We've talked a lot
about the creative mind,

145
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:07,022
and we agreed it needs a
certain freedom to explore.

146
00:10:07,189 --> 00:10:09,691
Take your freedom.
I can't live like this anymore.

147
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:12,235
It makes me feel worthless.
Calm yourself down.

148
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:15,363
Go set up home with Patel.
See if she does your tax returns.

149
00:10:15,531 --> 00:10:17,490
Do you love her? Is she young?

150
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:19,367
For heaven's sake...
Is she?!

151
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:21,411
Yes!

152
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:29,210
If you leave here tonight
to be with her, don't come back.

153
00:10:30,087 --> 00:10:33,340
Beth, you're making fools of us both.

154
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:36,509
Liar!

155
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:44,225
Fuck.

156
00:10:44,393 --> 00:10:48,521
I didn't know
they provided material too.

157
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:03,244
Beth does everything for him, you know.
Types his manuscript,

158
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:06,581
deals with his agent, makes his
female characters convincing.

159
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:09,042
She even came up with the name
Dr. Inchcombe.

160
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:11,586
No wonder he's bored.

161
00:11:11,754 --> 00:11:15,340
I hope she takes him
to the fucking cleaners.

162
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:29,354
At the end of the day,
this is why I'm glad I'm single.

163
00:11:42,576 --> 00:11:45,078
Will she take him back though?
That's the question.

164
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:47,288
Would you?
Well, I'd be torn.

165
00:11:47,456 --> 00:11:50,375
He's far too up himself.
Yeah, but what about their farm?

166
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:54,045
Splitting up all this?
Must be worth a fortune.

167
00:11:54,714 --> 00:11:56,965
Nadia Patel.

168
00:11:57,133 --> 00:12:01,052
"Gazelle eyes." "Tantric sex."

169
00:12:01,262 --> 00:12:04,055
She's very rash, making him choose.

170
00:12:04,932 --> 00:12:07,517
Why would he choose me?

171
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:14,691
I thought you weren't going to come.
I was busy. Rowing with my wife.

172
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:17,152
Where are we going?
Home.

173
00:12:17,319 --> 00:12:18,486
To your farm?

174
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:25,118
We could have gone on just as we were.

175
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:28,329
Yes, but you said
you wanted to be with me.

176
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:31,833
Yes. In London.

177
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:33,585
Now and then.

178
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:48,183
Big glass of Rioja, please.
And I need a room.

179
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:50,101
Sure. How many nights?

180
00:12:50,269 --> 00:12:52,353
Don't know. Just one?

181
00:12:52,521 --> 00:12:56,649
Are you here for the writers' retreat?
No, but I'm a writer.

182
00:12:56,817 --> 00:12:58,109
Well, journalist.

183
00:12:58,527 --> 00:13:01,946
I don't mean to pry.
I'm just really nosey.

184
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:03,948
I'm from here. Sort of.

185
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:07,202
Well, it's a nice place. I love it.

186
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:11,956
I keep meaning to leave, but...
Hard to get away.

187
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,042
My mom's house is just up the road.

188
00:13:14,210 --> 00:13:17,378
You're not staying with her?
She's... She died.

189
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:19,380
Have that on me.

190
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:22,967
And here's your key.

191
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:26,429
Up the stairs, right in front.
You can't miss it.

192
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:28,139
Thanks.

193
00:13:32,102 --> 00:13:35,188
Didn't think I'd see you tonight.

194
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:38,733
Bit of an atmosphere at Stonefield.
Tell me everything.

195
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:42,362
Marriage. Remind me never to try it.

196
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:46,950
Andy, you're just a sex object.
No one would have you.

197
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:14,435
So the Hardiments have
lived here for centuries?

198
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:17,772
No. About 20 years.

199
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:19,899
Still strangers, by local standards.

200
00:14:30,202 --> 00:14:32,954
Andy, come look at Ingrid.

201
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:35,498
I think she's coming into heat.

202
00:14:39,461 --> 00:14:41,462
She's very nice, Beth.

203
00:14:41,630 --> 00:14:44,465
Yeah. I owe her a lot.

204
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:47,677
Husband's kind of a sleazebag?

205
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:50,305
We'd say "prick" here, actually.

206
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:52,015
Or wanker.

207
00:14:52,308 --> 00:14:56,269
That's good.
We might even call him a fuck.

208
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:59,147
That's good too.

209
00:15:05,154 --> 00:15:08,823
Can I help?
It's going rotten underneath.

210
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:12,201
Can I have a look at Ingrid?
Look, it's... It's falling apart.

211
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:14,245
Yeah, well, I can do that. Beth...

212
00:15:15,998 --> 00:15:18,625
He won't last five minutes.

213
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:38,102
Jesus. He's been translated
into Icelandic and Swahili.

214
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:42,523
What an output.

215
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:45,902
I need my book to be a success.

216
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:50,239
I need a tiny reward
for all my endeavors.

217
00:15:53,369 --> 00:15:55,244
I need a dump.

218
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:15,139
- Beth.
- No, don't touch me.

219
00:16:15,307 --> 00:16:16,891
Don't you dare.
I'm sorry.

220
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:19,227
Not good enough, not anymore.
I'm sorry.

221
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:21,437
You do what you like,
then you're sorry?

222
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:24,232
I hate myself. I hate myself.

223
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,150
Where were you?

224
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:28,945
I drove her back to London.
Took all night.

225
00:16:29,113 --> 00:16:33,783
You drove her home?
I finished it. She was in a state.

226
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:38,454
- So it's over?
- I'm sorry.

227
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:42,709
I don't know why I'm like this.

228
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:46,421
I couldn't manage without you.

229
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:12,155
I've got to go to the bottle bank.

230
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:13,740
Okay.

231
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:17,994
- Let's talk later.
- Yeah.

232
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:22,123
- The goat's come into heat.
- Has it?

233
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:26,961
I love you so much.

234
00:17:27,629 --> 00:17:29,714
Me too.

235
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:55,573
I've just seen the Hardiments kiss
and make up.

236
00:17:55,741 --> 00:17:58,868
The hat's on.
Looks like she's taking him back.

237
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:02,330
When the hat's on,
it means don't speak.

238
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:06,626
So peace is restored.

239
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:10,463
For fuck's sake!

240
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:13,800
I don't like cows.
Yeah.

241
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:16,969
They exude bovine malice.
Yeah.

242
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:19,347
These girls are killing machines.

243
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:21,891
They don't like Americans either.
Very funny.

244
00:18:24,311 --> 00:18:25,812
It's Winnards Farm.

245
00:18:25,979 --> 00:18:29,273
Lady there died a while back.
Place is empty.

246
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:31,567
Think it's being robbed?
Nah.

247
00:18:31,985 --> 00:18:33,611
Probably just kids.

248
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:36,906
Nothing to do around here
except make trouble.

249
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:41,035
What if it's bad guys?

250
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:44,163
Don't you have a blunderbuss
or a fowling piece or something?

251
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:49,210
Used to belong to my dad, this place.

252
00:18:49,378 --> 00:18:52,004
Really?
But it all went tits up.

253
00:18:52,172 --> 00:18:55,591
The land was flogged to a consortium
