I used to watch you out of my window,

996
01:10:28,641 --> 01:10:31,351
helping your daughter
skateboard up the lane.

997
01:10:32,102 --> 01:10:34,312
Bit of an obvious crush, wasn't it?

998
01:10:34,813 --> 01:10:38,650
Is that why I'm here?
To expurgate the crush?

999
01:10:38,817 --> 01:10:40,318
I don't know.

1000
01:10:40,486 --> 01:10:42,403
Or as revenge on your ex?

1001
01:10:43,239 --> 01:10:45,615
I don't know, Nicholas.

1002
01:10:45,824 --> 01:10:46,991
Why are you here?

1003
01:10:48,285 --> 01:10:49,869
I should have thought
that was obvious.

1004
01:10:52,665 --> 01:10:56,292
Since you climbed over that stile
in the summer,

1005
01:10:57,127 --> 01:10:59,963
I haven't thought about
very much else.

1006
01:11:07,137 --> 01:11:09,764
When can we do this again?
What about Beth?

1007
01:11:09,932 --> 01:11:12,183
Beth and I have this kind of open...
Bullshit.

1008
01:11:12,351 --> 01:11:15,645
Thursday?
Isn't life complicated enough?

1009
01:11:15,813 --> 01:11:18,022
Don't put me in your column.

1010
01:11:18,691 --> 01:11:20,942
In your dreams.

1011
01:11:29,702 --> 01:11:31,869
Structure can be so sterile, can't it?

1012
01:11:32,037 --> 01:11:34,205
I always think of it
as a 3-dimensional...

1013
01:11:34,373 --> 01:11:36,207
Here he is.

1014
01:11:36,667 --> 01:11:40,753
Oh, poor you. Was it awful?
I was starting to worry.

1015
01:11:40,921 --> 01:11:45,133
Bloody terrible. Didn't move
till well past Chiswick, but look.

1016
01:11:45,301 --> 01:11:48,052
I popped into Fortnum's.
My favorite teas.

1017
01:11:51,265 --> 01:11:55,059
Oh, my goodness, you feel like my buzzy
toothbrush just after I've charged it up.

1018
01:11:55,227 --> 01:11:58,730
You should go to London more often.
Well, maybe I will.

1019
01:11:58,897 --> 01:12:02,483
Sorry, everybody. Traffic was a pig.
Do carry on. What have I missed?

1020
01:12:02,651 --> 01:12:05,903
Well, I'm trying this magic realist bit
at the end of Chapter 3.

1021
01:12:06,071 --> 01:12:08,406
That sounds very innovative.
You think so?

1022
01:12:08,574 --> 01:12:11,868
Yes. I think I've always been waiting
for the, magic realist crime novel.

1023
01:12:13,245 --> 01:12:16,247
Wuthering Heights, it's
kind of Angel of the North.

1024
01:12:28,177 --> 01:12:33,598
So after two years of radio silence,
I contact my editor,

1025
01:12:34,266 --> 01:12:37,852
and she loves... I mean, she loves
the chapters I did in the fall.

1026
01:12:38,020 --> 01:12:40,605
Oh, Glen.

1027
01:12:41,273 --> 01:12:42,899
I tried writing at the library

1028
01:12:43,067 --> 01:12:46,444
but I could feel that awful paralysis
descending again.

1029
01:12:46,612 --> 01:12:50,782
I missed everything that I've been,
you know, finding here.

1030
01:12:51,158 --> 01:12:53,284
Oh, my God.

1031
01:12:53,452 --> 01:12:56,245
It's so beautiful.

1032
01:12:56,413 --> 01:12:58,122
Well, I'm very glad you've come back.

1033
01:12:58,290 --> 01:13:00,124
Yeah, in a few solid weeks...

1034
01:13:00,292 --> 01:13:02,460
Holy cow!

1035
01:13:04,463 --> 01:13:06,339
Idiots!

1036
01:13:06,799 --> 01:13:08,299
Morons!

1037
01:13:12,346 --> 01:13:16,099
Hey, writers, let's egg
the self-regarding sacks of shit.

1038
01:13:16,266 --> 01:13:19,310
It's half term, they're just bored.

1039
01:13:21,688 --> 01:13:24,524
There's this theory that Hardy
gave his wife syphilis, you know.

1040
01:13:24,691 --> 01:13:27,485
No evidence, but the symptoms fit.
Poor woman,

1041
01:13:27,653 --> 01:13:31,406
she starts to get eccentric and then
she moves her bed up to their attic.

1042
01:13:31,573 --> 01:13:32,615
The bastard.

1043
01:13:32,783 --> 01:13:35,827
Meanwhile, Hardy falls in love with
a woman 39 years younger than him.

1044
01:13:35,994 --> 01:13:39,789
I don't believe it.
Yeah, he was 65 and she was 26.

1045
01:13:39,957 --> 01:13:42,500
Geoff.
Glen.

1046
01:13:42,668 --> 01:13:44,168
Henry James?
Thomas Hardy.

1047
01:13:44,336 --> 01:13:47,338
That's it, a Hardy book.
Coming well?

1048
01:13:47,506 --> 01:13:50,091
Yes, actually.
He gave his wife syphilis.

1049
01:13:50,259 --> 01:13:52,301
Jolly good.

1050
01:13:54,346 --> 01:13:56,389
He's completely distracted.

1051
01:13:56,557 --> 01:13:58,516
He's up and down to London
all the time.

1052
01:13:58,684 --> 01:14:01,853
This latest Inchcombe's
taking everything he's got.

1053
01:14:02,271 --> 01:14:04,647
It's really preying on him.

1054
01:14:06,191 --> 01:14:08,568
Is it any good?
Because I keep changing things

1055
01:14:08,735 --> 01:14:09,777
and...

1056
01:14:15,701 --> 01:14:18,161
It's brutally candid.

1057
01:14:18,954 --> 01:14:22,457
You lay yourself completely bare.

1058
01:14:25,544 --> 01:14:30,548
It's a bit over-written.
It needs a good edit, but,

1059
01:14:32,092 --> 01:14:33,634
it's very moving.

1060
01:14:34,970 --> 01:14:36,471
Thank you.

1061
01:14:36,638 --> 01:14:38,389
So,

1062
01:14:39,224 --> 01:14:41,058
have I done my duty?

1063
01:14:41,435 --> 01:14:43,060
Admirably.

1064
01:14:43,479 --> 01:14:45,563
Now do I get my treat?

1065
01:14:47,232 --> 01:14:49,901
You are so cheesy.

1066
01:14:56,408 --> 01:14:59,076
Zero Ben sightings
in two whole months.

1067
01:14:59,244 --> 01:15:04,165
Last time I saw Plastic,
she looked like a minger.

1068
01:15:04,333 --> 01:15:06,167
All red-eyed and gutted.

1069
01:15:06,376 --> 01:15:08,169
Ben's a love rat.

1070
01:15:08,337 --> 01:15:10,213
You gotta face it, she should move on.

1071
01:15:10,380 --> 01:15:11,923
She's probably topped herself.

1072
01:15:12,257 --> 01:15:16,552
I would, if Ben dumped me.
Jode, don't say that.

1073
01:15:16,720 --> 01:15:18,596
What if she's done something?

1074
01:15:18,764 --> 01:15:21,474
Like got in the bath
with her heated tongs?

1075
01:15:21,642 --> 01:15:24,769
Like taken a stack of pills.
Think she might be lying there,

1076
01:15:24,937 --> 01:15:27,688
all choked in vomit and drug froth?
That'd be dire.

1077
01:15:27,856 --> 01:15:30,733
If we find her, we'll get in the papers.
Oh, my God.

1078
01:15:30,901 --> 01:15:32,777
Rock chick dead at Winnards Farm.

1079
01:15:49,253 --> 01:15:51,420
What's Uncle Andy doing here?

1080
01:16:03,850 --> 01:16:05,977
Ass biscuits.

1081
01:16:15,696 --> 01:16:17,488
No answer.

1082
01:16:17,656 --> 01:16:20,992
She could've been there days.
She could be all putrid-like, rancid.

1083
01:16:21,159 --> 01:16:23,160
Oh, no, gonna chuck.

1084
01:16:23,328 --> 01:16:27,123
All bloated and all greeny.
Uncle Andy will find her by the smell.

1085
01:16:30,460 --> 01:16:31,752
Andy.

1086
01:16:31,920 --> 01:16:35,131
- Bollocks, she's alive.
- Haven't seen you for a while.

1087
01:16:35,716 --> 01:16:38,009
Thought you might be ill
or something, or depressed.

1088
01:16:38,176 --> 01:16:40,428
I've had my head down, writing.

1089
01:16:40,596 --> 01:16:41,679
Come for a drink.

1090
01:16:42,222 --> 01:16:44,432
Let's lighten up.
I'd love to, but,

1091
01:16:45,434 --> 01:16:48,603
I'm kind of on one with my writing,
and...

1092
01:16:49,938 --> 01:16:51,480
Can we do it soon, though?

1093
01:16:51,648 --> 01:16:55,192
I really would like to.
Just not right now.

1094
01:16:55,861 --> 01:16:57,486
Sure.

1095
01:17:08,040 --> 01:17:09,874
What is he doing here?

1096
01:17:10,042 --> 01:17:12,001
He just came by on the off-chance.

1097
01:17:12,169 --> 01:17:14,045
Off-chance of what?

1098
01:17:14,212 --> 01:17:16,631
Something about the roofing
for the shed.

1099
01:17:22,971 --> 01:17:25,306
Do you think he's in with a chance?
No way.

1100
01:17:25,474 --> 01:17:28,476
Why not? He's fit. I'd do him.
Jody, he's my uncle.

1101
01:17:28,644 --> 01:17:31,646
She'd be mad not to have him.
Bet he goes like a train.

1102
01:17:38,528 --> 01:17:40,071
Let's go, my knickers are wet.

1103
01:17:40,238 --> 01:17:42,365
Wait, wait.

1104
01:17:46,078 --> 01:17:48,996
Oh, my God.

1105
01:17:52,918 --> 01:17:54,251
Nicholas, go.

1106
01:18:02,761 --> 01:18:05,680
"Prolific author
of intelligent crime novels."

1107
01:18:05,847 --> 01:18:08,766
Fucking D-list.
How could she do that after Ben?

1108
01:18:08,934 --> 01:18:12,103
He's not even a proper celeb.
Maybe she's numbing the pain.

1109
01:18:12,270 --> 01:18:13,312
Trying to tear love...

1110
01:18:13,480 --> 01:18:15,147
Shut up, Case.
She's just a slag.

1111
01:18:15,315 --> 01:18:18,109
She went out and pulled a married man.

1112
01:18:18,652 --> 01:18:21,904
Like that bitch
that went off with my dad.

1113
01:18:23,448 --> 01:18:26,534
I know who I feel sorry for.

1114
01:18:30,872 --> 01:18:33,499
Then there'll be the divorce
and acrimony,

1115
01:18:33,667 --> 01:18:36,419
and Beth's world will fall apart.
Yeah.

1116
01:18:36,586 --> 01:18:40,715
But maybe one day,
she'll put the bitterness behind her,

1117
01:18:40,882 --> 01:18:42,133
and find a new love.

1118
01:18:42,300 --> 01:18:45,052
Don't be daft. She's old, you sop.

1119
01:18:45,220 --> 01:18:46,971
See?

1120
01:18:47,681 --> 01:18:50,474
That's D-list's car.

1121
01:18:52,060 --> 01:18:55,312
This is where he hides his car
when he goes to shag Plastic.

1122
01:18:55,480 --> 01:18:58,524
Yeah. Dirty git.
Big old turd.

1123
01:18:58,692 --> 01:19:02,319
He's a rotten cheater.
Like my dad.

1124
01:19:03,321 --> 01:19:06,490
Come on, Case. Let's fuck him up.

1125
01:19:10,620 --> 01:19:13,497
Shit salad.

1126
01:19:16,835 --> 01:19:19,962
Oh, poor you.
What a drag.

1127
01:19:20,338 --> 01:19:21,589
Yes, it's a frightful bore.

1128
01:19:21,757 --> 01:19:23,382
I'll hold off on the paella then.

1129
01:19:23,550 --> 01:19:25,468
You're a marvel. See you soon.

1130
01:19:25,635 --> 01:19:27,261
Did you...?

1131
01:19:30,432 --> 01:19:33,392
Beth, can I use the printer?

1132
01:19:33,560 --> 01:19:37,354
Nicholas is stuck on the motorway
with a flat tire,

1133
01:19:37,814 --> 01:19:40,024
but I couldn't hear traffic,
just rooks.

1134
01:19:42,360 --> 01:19:44,361
Sorry, um, did you want me
to read something?

1135
01:19:44,529 --> 01:19:46,530
No. Can I use the printer?

1136
01:19:50,535 --> 01:19:54,497
Nicholas, someone knows.

1137
01:19:54,706 --> 01:19:57,666
Maybe we should...
Who cares?

1138
01:20:07,052 --> 01:20:11,388
Casey, pop them. Pop them.

1139
01:20:16,228 --> 01:20:19,104
Fucking bingo.

1140
01:20:23,860 --> 01:20:26,111
Hello, Casey, how are you? Hello.

1141
01:20:26,279 --> 01:20:28,364
All right.
Waiting for the bus?

1142
01:20:28,532 --> 01:20:30,407
Bus got scrapped.
So it did.

1143
01:20:30,575 --> 01:20:33,828
Well, hope it doesn't rain.

1144
01:20:35,455 --> 01:20:38,457
Gutted for her.
Me too.

1145
01:20:39,125 --> 01:20:41,627
Fat arse though, hasn't she?

1146
01:20:45,006 --> 01:20:46,757
Send her the photo, Case.
I can't.

1147
01:20:46,925 --> 01:20:48,968
Why not?
What if it ruins her life?

1148
01:20:49,135 --> 01:20:51,220
We gotta do something.
Plastic's an idiot.

1149
01:20:51,388 --> 01:20:54,223
She fucked it up with Ben.
We fucked it up with Ben, Jode.

1150
01:20:57,269 --> 01:20:59,186
It's like...

1151
01:21:01,773 --> 01:21:04,608
We've gotta rescue her from D-list.

1152
01:21:33,972 --> 01:21:35,639
Casey.
What?

1153
01:21:35,807 --> 01:21:39,977
She's back in touch with him.
She's got an e-mail from Ben.

1154
01:21:40,270 --> 01:21:43,480
"Tamara, Fran's baby has come."

1155
01:21:43,648 --> 01:21:46,984
Case, he says it's a little brown girl
with curly black hair.

1156
01:21:47,152 --> 01:21:48,569
Cute.

1157
01:21:48,737 --> 01:21:52,823
"I think we can safely say
it's Steven Culley's, not mine.

1158
01:21:52,991 --> 01:21:55,492
Truth is, I feel free.

1159
01:21:55,660 --> 01:21:57,870
Gig in Paris for a few days.

1160
01:21:58,038 --> 01:22:01,165
If I bring him down,
would you have Boss?"

1161
01:22:01,333 --> 01:22:05,002
Yes. Yes, he's coming back.

1162
01:22:05,337 --> 01:22:07,630
What are you doing?
Dear, Ben,

1163
01:22:07,797 --> 01:22:11,508
I have found a reliable dog lover
in the village.

1164
01:22:11,676 --> 01:22:13,552
Who?
Please call Jody,

1165
01:22:13,720 --> 01:22:17,598
You can't send that.
On 07700-900-929.

1166
01:22:17,766 --> 01:22:20,684
I'm getting him back down here!
For who? You?

1167
01:22:20,852 --> 01:22:23,020
Why not me?
Are you mental?

1168
01:22:23,188 --> 01:22:25,814
"Reliable dog lover"?
You're making a great big mess...

1169
01:22:25,982 --> 01:22:28,359
I'm making something happen!

1170
01:22:28,693 --> 01:22:30,527
Otherwise, my whole life will go by,

1171
01:22:30,695 --> 01:22:33,072
and I'll be 34
and washed up like my mom.

1172
01:22:33,239 --> 01:22:36,367
And no one decent
will ever even have snogged me.

1173
01:22:36,534 --> 01:22:39,370
If you do this, you're on your own.

1174
01:22:39,537 --> 01:22:41,705
Fuck off, then.

1175
01:22:42,207 --> 01:22:44,500
You twat.

1176
01:22:47,879 --> 01:22:50,965
There's the festival brochure.
You're on in the Lanson marquee.

1177
01:22:51,257 --> 01:22:53,884
And, um, I've marked a few bits,
in case you want to read.

1178
01:22:54,052 --> 01:22:57,012
You're a marvel. Cheers.

1179
01:22:57,180 --> 01:22:58,847
I could come with you.

1180
01:22:59,015 --> 01:23:01,225
Don't. You hate festivals.

1181
01:23:01,393 --> 01:23:04,353
But it's only Hadditon. I'll come.

1182
01:23:04,521 --> 01:23:07,398
It'll be completely boring.
You'll hate it.

1183
01:23:07,565 --> 01:23:09,441
Stay here.

1184
01:23:30,880 --> 01:23:35,092
Wanker! Right.

1185
01:23:37,095 --> 01:23:38,637
Finished.

1186
01:23:38,805 --> 01:23:41,640
I'm doing this cake in celebration.
Well done.

1187
01:23:41,808 --> 01:23:43,142
Well, to Hardy.

1188
01:23:44,519 --> 01:23:48,147
Yeah, even though I can't bear
the man for what he did to his wife.

1189
01:23:48,523 --> 01:23:51,775
Thanks, Andy.
Just pop them over there.

1190
01:23:57,407 --> 01:24:00,034
How do I find out who sent this?

1191
01:24:05,540 --> 01:24:07,916
It says "number withheld."

1192
01:24:10,462 --> 01:24:12,379
Did you know?

1193
01:24:15,508 --> 01:24:17,801
I couldn't tell you.

1194
01:24:18,136 --> 01:24:19,970
I'm sorry, Beth.

1195
01:24:26,269 --> 01:24:28,062
Her.

1196
01:24:28,480 --> 01:24:30,397
Oh, my God.

1197
01:24:30,565 --> 01:24:33,609
This is just...
This is just horrible.

1198
01:24:33,777 --> 01:24:34,818
Right under my nose.

1199
01:24:34,986 --> 01:24:36,820
It's so shitty.
God, I feel sick.

1200
01:24:36,988 --> 01:24:39,823
So insulting. You do not deserve
to be treated like this.

1201
01:24:39,991 --> 01:24:41,658
If you're kind to me, I'll cry.

1202
01:24:41,826 --> 01:24:44,703
And I don't want to cry,
I must be very clear.

1203
01:24:45,163 --> 01:24:47,581
If there's anything that I can do...

1204
01:24:47,832 --> 01:24:50,084
I have to do it by myself.

1205
01:24:54,172 --> 01:24:56,840
Come on. Come on, Beth.
Come on.

1206
01:24:57,008 --> 01:24:59,927
I trod in the sponge mix.

1207
01:25:06,226 --> 01:25:09,103
Jody? This is Ben Sergeant.

1208
01:25:10,021 --> 01:25:11,980
Yeah, that's right. I love dogs.

1209
01:25:12,565 --> 01:25:16,318
Yeah, so I'll see you
at Winnards Farm at 2:00.

1210
01:25:16,486 --> 01:25:18,946
Yeah. Perfect.

1211
01:25:27,622 --> 01:25:29,373
Andy.

1212
01:25:29,582 --> 01:25:32,292
Hey, how are you?

1213
01:25:34,045 --> 01:25:37,047
I wondered if you wanted
to go for that drink?

1214
01:25:37,549 --> 01:25:40,384
I need a friend at the mo...
You and Nicholas Hardiment.

1215
01:25:40,552 --> 01:25:42,761
That's a nice piece of work, isn't it?

1216
01:25:42,929 --> 01:25:46,890
I get it from his point of view.
He's always been a cheating wanker.

1217
01:25:47,058 --> 01:25:49,810
Loves having his cake and eating it.

1218
01:25:50,895 --> 01:25:53,856
But since when did your standards
drop so low?

1219
01:25:54,023 --> 01:25:55,315
You could have anyone.

1220
01:25:55,483 --> 01:25:58,235
All you have to do is bat your eyes.
Andy.

1221
01:25:58,403 --> 01:26:02,322
I care a lot about Beth.
She helped me out when I was at rock bottom.

1222
01:26:02,490 --> 01:26:04,032
I'm not going to split them up.

1223
01:26:04,200 --> 01:26:05,993
It's just...
A bit of fun?

1224
01:26:06,161 --> 01:26:09,079
It's none of your bloody business.

1225
01:26:11,249 --> 01:26:13,750
Andy Cobb knows.
Cock pie. Has he told Beth?

1226
01:26:13,918 --> 01:26:16,587
I don't know, but he might.
And I wouldn't blame him.

1227
01:26:16,754 --> 01:26:18,213
I suppose it has to come out sometime.

1228
01:26:18,381 --> 01:26:19,423
Does it?

1229
01:26:19,591 --> 01:26:22,551
It's a good thing. Feels like a relief.
It means we can think about

1230
01:26:22,719 --> 01:26:24,803
our plans for the future.
What future?

1231
01:26:24,971 --> 01:26:27,514
I know it's been hard for you,
sharing me with Beth.

1232
01:26:27,682 --> 01:26:29,808
But I'm yours now.
I'm gonna leave her.

1233
01:26:29,976 --> 01:26:32,936
Mr. Hardiment. It's time.

1234
01:26:34,230 --> 01:26:38,108
I want a new life with you.

1235
01:26:41,279 --> 01:26:42,529
It's a nice dog, Mom.

1236
01:26:42,697 --> 01:26:46,033
Well, I don't like having dog hair
and slobber all over the place.

1237
01:26:46,201 --> 01:26:47,534
But I said yes.

1238
01:26:47,702 --> 01:26:50,287
No dogs, no way, and that's final.

1239
01:26:50,455 --> 01:26:54,583
You loser, I hate you!
You want to ruin my life!

1240
01:26:56,294 --> 01:26:57,961
Live the dream, Jody.

1241
01:26:58,129 --> 01:26:59,713
Well, it all runs very smoothly.

1242
01:26:59,881 --> 01:27:03,133
I start a book in the summer
and publish it the following spring.

1243
01:27:03,301 --> 01:27:05,302
Bit of a factory, really.

1244
01:27:06,679 --> 01:27:10,807
So you've finished Like The Night, which
is the 17th of the Inchcombe adventures.

1245
01:27:10,975 --> 01:27:14,144
And we all assume
you're planning the next one already.

1246
01:27:14,312 --> 01:27:16,063
Well,

1247
01:27:17,315 --> 01:27:19,358
there isn't gonna be a next one.

1248
01:27:19,525 --> 01:27:20,651
- No.
- What?

1249
01:27:20,818 --> 01:27:22,986
Frankly,
I'm sick to death of Inchcombe.

1250
01:27:23,154 --> 01:27:25,781
In fact, I'm about to kill him off.

1251
01:27:25,949 --> 01:27:27,366
- No.
- He can't do that.

1252
01:27:27,533 --> 01:27:29,785
Well, I think
that's what we call in the trade,

1253
01:27:29,953 --> 01:27:32,913
a bit of a bombshell,
for your fans here.

1254
01:27:33,456 --> 01:27:37,542
Yes, but I'm moving on
to fresh pastures.

1255
01:27:37,710 --> 01:27:39,503
No.

1256
01:27:39,671 --> 01:27:41,922
Inchcombe is about to meet
a very sticky end,

1257
01:27:42,090 --> 01:27:45,175
and it's one murder
I'm really looking forward to.

1258
01:27:46,552 --> 01:27:49,972
Now, at this point, we should
get some questions, I think.

1259
01:27:50,139 --> 01:27:53,934
And I'm...
Yes, there's a lady over there.

1260
01:27:57,272 --> 01:28:02,276
You write a lot about adultery,
is that from personal experience?

1261
01:28:03,403 --> 01:28:04,945
Madam,

1262
01:28:06,948 --> 01:28:08,949
what a saucy question. Uh...

1263
01:28:09,117 --> 01:28:11,702
But there's no need for an author's
work to be autobiographical...

1264
01:28:11,869 --> 01:28:13,704
Why do you cheat persistently
on your wife?

1265
01:28:15,373 --> 01:28:17,249
Who's that?

1266
01:28:22,714 --> 01:28:24,840
Because she lets me.

1267
01:28:26,217 --> 01:28:27,968
Tamara.

1268
01:28:28,970 --> 01:28:31,263
Where...?
Nicholas, this has got to stop.

1269
01:28:31,431 --> 01:28:33,640
You're right. I can't go on using her.
Lying to her.

1270
01:28:33,808 --> 01:28:35,225
It won't be fun but I've gotta do it.

1271
01:28:35,393 --> 01:28:38,145
I don't feel alive with Beth.
I haven't been living for years.

1272
01:28:38,313 --> 01:28:41,356
She's smothered me like a blanket.
Nicholas, listen to me.

1273
01:28:41,524 --> 01:28:45,277
It was fun,
but it's wrong and it's over.

1274
01:28:48,364 --> 01:28:51,033
I'm in love with you.
I'm sorry.

1275
01:28:51,200 --> 01:28:52,576
No.

1276
01:28:52,744 --> 01:28:56,204
No. No. No. You can't end it.
Tamara...

1277
01:28:56,372 --> 01:28:58,415
Fuck supper!
Will you keep it down?

1278
01:28:58,583 --> 01:29:01,001
My God, you're cold-hearted.
No, I'm not.

1279
01:29:01,169 --> 01:29:03,962
You don't feel a thing, do you?
I do. I do feel.

1280
01:29:04,130 --> 01:29:07,341
I feel like I'm blazing away inside
all the time.

1281
01:29:07,967 --> 01:29:11,261
Why do I do these things?
What am I doing with you?

1282
01:29:12,597 --> 01:29:15,724
There's someone else, isn't there?
For God's sake.

1283
01:29:15,892 --> 01:29:18,602
Not the narcissist drummer?
Goodbye.

1284
01:29:18,770 --> 01:29:20,479
It's that ignorant lunk, isn't it?

1285
01:29:20,646 --> 01:29:23,523
That muscle-bound wastrel
Andy Cobb.

1286
01:29:23,983 --> 01:29:27,277
Andy Cobb is a far better man
than you.

1287
01:29:30,865 --> 01:29:32,491
Go on.

1288
01:29:36,829 --> 01:29:40,582
Mr. Hardiment, will you sign this?
Imagine getting him to sign.

1289
01:29:40,750 --> 01:29:43,251
I love your books.

1290
01:29:59,852 --> 01:30:01,812
Thank you.

1291
01:30:09,695 --> 01:30:11,488
Hello?

1292
01:30:14,200 --> 01:30:16,993
It's Jody Long about the dog.

1293
01:30:21,040 --> 01:30:22,749
Ben?

1294
01:30:28,131 --> 01:30:29,840
Hello?

1295
01:30:32,718 --> 01:30:34,318
Ben?

1296
01:30:56,701 --> 01:30:58,702
Well, you gonna answer that?

1297
01:30:59,954 --> 01:31:02,414
Jody, what are you doing
not fucking answering?

1298
01:31:06,210 --> 01:31:10,213
Ben's dog is here. It's loose.
It means Ben must be up at Winnards.

1299
01:31:12,300 --> 01:31:13,550
Boss!

1300
01:31:15,219 --> 01:31:16,553
Dog minder?

1301
01:31:17,763 --> 01:31:22,058
You've been breaking in, sending
e-mails and fucking people off.

1302
01:31:23,394 --> 01:31:26,730
Did you nick my black T-shirt?
I just wanted to meet you. Just once.

1303
01:31:26,898 --> 01:31:29,983
Just to tell you stuff.
Stuff? What stuff?

1304
01:31:30,151 --> 01:31:32,235
Like, I love you.

1305
01:31:32,904 --> 01:31:35,405
I really, really love you.

1306
01:31:35,865 --> 01:31:38,575
That's really nice.

1307
01:31:39,827 --> 01:31:43,121
I used to lie awake
thinking about you being here.

1308
01:31:43,289 --> 01:31:44,956
In Ewedown.

1309
01:31:45,124 --> 01:31:48,418
In the bum-hole of nowhere.

1310
01:31:49,420 --> 01:31:52,172
When you left, I couldn't bear it.

1311
01:31:52,548 --> 01:31:55,884
I just wanted to make you come back.

1312
01:32:00,431 --> 01:32:05,227
Do you still love me, Jody?
Even though I wanna lock you up?

1313
01:32:06,562 --> 01:32:08,647
What would you do for me then?

1314
01:32:09,398 --> 01:32:11,566
Would you do anything,
like a proper fan?

1315
01:32:13,027 --> 01:32:15,153
Let's see then, shall we?

1316
01:32:16,447 --> 01:32:18,447
I bet that bitch wants a baby.
Well, she'll find out.

1317
01:32:18,472 --> 01:32:19,672
Nicholas doesn't do children.

1318
01:32:19,867 --> 01:32:21,785
He'll leave it all up to her.

1319
01:32:21,953 --> 01:32:23,578
That'll age her.
Beth.

1320
01:32:23,746 --> 01:32:26,289
Suppose he discovers fatherhood?
They do, these men.

1321
01:32:26,457 --> 01:32:30,335
Second time around,
they get all nappy-happy.

1322
01:32:30,503 --> 01:32:32,295
I was barely 20 when I got pregnant.

1323
01:32:32,463 --> 01:32:35,799
I've never done anything. God.
Yes, you have. Look at this place.

1324
01:32:35,967 --> 01:32:38,176
I've let him walk all over me.
Why? Why have I done that?

1325
01:32:38,344 --> 01:32:39,719
I've wasted my life.

1326
01:32:39,887 --> 01:32:41,680
No. What about the work
you've done here?

1327
01:32:41,847 --> 01:32:42,889
Work?
Yes.

1328
01:32:43,057 --> 01:32:46,059
What, breeding goats?
Baking fucking biscuits?

1329
01:32:46,227 --> 01:32:47,561
It's meaningless!

1330
01:32:48,980 --> 01:32:50,438
Beth.

1331
01:32:50,648 --> 01:32:53,733
When I was lost with my book,
you helped me more than you know.

1332
01:32:53,901 --> 01:32:56,152
You asked me who I was writing it for.

1333
01:32:56,988 --> 01:32:58,655
You.

1334
01:33:21,512 --> 01:33:23,305
Excuse me.

1335
01:33:26,058 --> 01:33:27,642
May I speak with my wife?

1336
01:33:27,810 --> 01:33:31,104
No, you may not.

1337
01:33:32,773 --> 01:33:35,108
Beth. Beth.

1338
01:33:36,861 --> 01:33:38,653
It's over.

1339
01:33:39,572 --> 01:33:41,281
I've finished it.

1340
01:33:41,449 --> 01:33:43,700
She's been chasing me.

1341
01:33:43,868 --> 01:33:46,161
I think there's something
unhinged about her.

1342
01:33:46,329 --> 01:33:47,787
This wild crush.

1343
01:33:49,165 --> 01:33:53,293
Ben Sergeant's bloody dog again.
Go on, get out.

1344
01:33:53,461 --> 01:33:57,756
Back to that tart at Winnards Farm.
Go on. Bugger off!

1345
01:33:58,716 --> 01:34:00,216
Beth.

1346
01:34:01,510 --> 01:34:03,219
You know I'm sorry.

1347
01:34:04,055 --> 01:34:07,057
I want you to leave. I want a divorce.

1348
01:34:07,224 --> 01:34:09,225
No, you don't. Don't be ridiculous.

1349
01:34:09,644 --> 01:34:11,478
Now, look...
And I want this place.

1350
01:34:12,271 --> 01:34:13,396
You can't.

1351
01:34:13,898 --> 01:34:17,359
Watch me. I will.

1352
01:34:18,736 --> 01:34:22,781
That's it, lovely. Keep it going, keep it going.
Stop. Couple of sugars.

1353
01:34:24,617 --> 01:34:26,284
Stir it.

1354
01:34:35,503 --> 01:34:38,922
That is a very good cup of tea.
Which is lucky for you, Jody.

1355
01:34:39,090 --> 01:34:40,131
Had it been shit,

1356
01:34:40,299 --> 01:34:42,884
I'd be on the phone to the extremely
scary local cops right now.

1357
01:34:43,052 --> 01:34:44,427
Please don't tell my mom.

1358
01:34:44,595 --> 01:34:47,180
I know it's boring round here,
but for fuck's sakes.

1359
01:34:47,348 --> 01:34:48,932
I'm gonna get out soon as I can.

1360
01:34:49,100 --> 01:34:52,602
I'm gonna work in Vegas as a croupier.
Vegas or a cruise liner.

1361
01:34:53,562 --> 01:34:57,941
Aim high, Jody.
That's what I say. Aim high.

1362
01:35:04,782 --> 01:35:06,616
Ben?

1363
01:35:09,328 --> 01:35:12,455
You've had an infestation.
Of what?

1364
01:35:12,748 --> 01:35:14,374
Jody.

1365
01:35:35,646 --> 01:35:37,981
Hey, Greg!

1366
01:35:38,149 --> 01:35:41,151
I want a word with you.
It's Glen, asshole.

1367
01:35:41,318 --> 01:35:43,987
You fucking devious bastard.

1368
01:35:44,155 --> 01:35:46,448
I'm devious? I'm a bastard?

1369
01:35:46,615 --> 01:35:50,577
You think I haven't noticed
you've been worming your way in?

1370
01:35:50,745 --> 01:35:55,415
You keep your hands off my wife,
you low-rent pedant.

1371
01:35:56,500 --> 01:35:59,377
You've abused Beth long enough
with all of your goddamn lies.

1372
01:35:59,545 --> 01:36:01,004
I want you out of my house.

1373
01:36:01,172 --> 01:36:04,257
It's Beth's. She made this place.
And I fucking paid for it.

1374
01:36:04,425 --> 01:36:06,760
I've given Beth all this.
What can you give her?

1375
01:36:06,927 --> 01:36:10,972
I can give her integrity.
Obscure literary shit,

1376
01:36:11,140 --> 01:36:12,557
not worth 10 pence.

1377
01:36:12,725 --> 01:36:16,519
You know, if I made my fortune
fantasizing about rapes and murders,

1378
01:36:16,687 --> 01:36:18,021
I wouldn't be so proud.

1379
01:36:18,189 --> 01:36:21,524
You cretin.
Fuck you.

1380
01:36:22,067 --> 01:36:23,651
Beth will come to her senses.

1381
01:36:23,819 --> 01:36:28,114
You need an income to run Stonefield,
and mine's bigger than yours.

1382
01:36:35,206 --> 01:36:39,918
Get up, Nicholas, come on.
Let's talk about this like grown men.

1383
01:36:46,175 --> 01:36:48,968
Oh, my God. Nicholas.

1384
01:36:49,345 --> 01:36:50,553
Nic...

1385
01:36:50,763 --> 01:36:53,181
Get up.

1386
01:37:01,398 --> 01:37:03,733
Nicholas, get up.

1387
01:37:04,151 --> 01:37:06,736
Run. Come on. Get up.

1388
01:37:13,410 --> 01:37:15,703
Nicholas. Nicholas.

1389
01:37:51,615 --> 01:37:53,366
It was you?

1390
01:37:54,618 --> 01:37:56,661
It was you who sent the e-mail?

1391
01:37:56,829 --> 01:38:00,123
Jody's explained that she did it
out of a deep love for me.

1392
01:38:04,295 --> 01:38:07,630
Tammy.
Ben.

1393
01:38:18,475 --> 01:38:21,144
I think you should have this back.

1394
01:38:21,812 --> 01:38:23,771
I'm sorry.

1395
01:38:25,190 --> 01:38:27,817
Jody! The dog!

1396
01:39:12,237 --> 01:39:16,157
Got him. The beast.

1397
01:39:44,478 --> 01:39:46,229
Nicholas.

1398
01:39:48,774 --> 01:39:52,151
God. Oh, God. Nicholas.

1399
01:39:52,319 --> 01:39:54,070
Bitch. Brazen.

1400
01:39:54,863 --> 01:39:56,197
Brazen.
Beth.

1401
01:39:56,365 --> 01:39:59,951
That is brazen.
Beth, don't look! Please, don't look!

1402
01:40:04,123 --> 01:40:06,040
Nicholas?!

1403
01:40:12,423 --> 01:40:13,423
No!

1404
01:40:13,590 --> 01:40:17,593
No, but you can see it.
It's broken. It's smashed.

1405
01:40:18,846 --> 01:40:22,724
No, I haven't, but it's obvious.

1406
01:40:24,560 --> 01:40:28,229
Yes, his wife. Yes, she is.

1407
01:40:28,397 --> 01:40:31,149
Thank you. Thank you, I will.

1408
01:40:32,735 --> 01:40:34,777
They're on their way.

1409
01:40:36,572 --> 01:40:38,448
Beth, help is coming.

1410
01:40:46,623 --> 01:40:48,541
It's broken.

1411
01:41:18,739 --> 01:41:20,364
Tamara.

1412
01:41:21,992 --> 01:41:23,659
Listen.

1413
01:41:26,163 --> 01:41:28,331
I'm sorry.

1414
01:41:29,833 --> 01:41:31,667
Come on.

1415
01:41:31,835 --> 01:41:34,253
Are you blaming yourself?

1416
01:41:36,340 --> 01:41:37,673
It was an accident.

1417
01:41:52,940 --> 01:41:55,358
I'd better get back up to Stonefield.

1418
01:41:55,776 --> 01:41:59,487
Come with me. We'll get this sorted.

1419
01:42:04,535 --> 01:42:07,328
Then get Ben
to take you back to London.

1420
01:42:07,955 --> 01:42:10,540
I don't want to be with Ben.

1421
01:42:27,266 --> 01:42:29,600
Put it on the back seat right here.

1422
01:42:41,446 --> 01:42:42,446
What are you doing?

1423
01:42:42,614 --> 01:42:45,032
I figured it was best,
you know, that I take off.

1424
01:42:45,200 --> 01:42:47,410
She doesn't want writers
around the place now.

1425
01:42:47,578 --> 01:42:49,704
And police, autopsies, not my thing.

1426
01:42:49,872 --> 01:42:52,248
You can't run away.
I'm not running away.

1427
01:42:52,416 --> 01:42:56,586
I've finished my book.
My time here is up. Destiny calls.

1428
01:42:56,753 --> 01:43:00,339
Beth is asking for you.
Really?

1429
01:43:00,591 --> 01:43:02,925
She's on her own over there.

1430
01:43:03,510 --> 01:43:08,181
Glen, she doesn't need a writer
around the place,

1431
01:43:08,682 --> 01:43:10,766
she needs a man.

1432
01:43:19,651 --> 01:43:21,986
I'm so sorry.

1433
01:43:23,614 --> 01:43:26,115
It was my fault. I let the dog go.

1434
01:43:26,283 --> 01:43:28,367
No. No.
I shooed him away.

1435
01:43:28,535 --> 01:43:31,787
The police said it was an accident,
but if I'd caught him, tied him up...

1436
01:43:31,955 --> 01:43:33,164
No, it wasn't your fault.

1437
01:43:33,332 --> 01:43:36,542
What I don't understand is why was
Nicholas in that field anyway?

1438
01:43:36,710 --> 01:43:39,170
He hated cows.
And when he saw them coming,

1439
01:43:39,338 --> 01:43:44,091
why didn't he get out of their way...?
Beth, I have to tell you that...

1440
01:43:56,647 --> 01:43:58,773
You live in the country.

1441
01:43:58,941 --> 01:44:01,025
You share it
with those dangerous beasts,

1442
01:44:01,193 --> 01:44:03,945
and when they get scared, they run.

1443
01:44:04,112 --> 01:44:06,113
Like we do.

1444
01:44:07,574 --> 01:44:09,158
Oh, Glen.

1445
01:44:12,496 --> 01:44:14,580
Stay with me.

1446
01:44:48,782 --> 01:44:51,450
Kind of suits you.
Don't say anything.

1447
01:44:51,618 --> 01:44:53,953
I always did like the old one.

1448
01:44:57,207 --> 01:45:00,126
You did it on purpose, didn't you?
What?

1449
01:45:00,294 --> 01:45:03,337
Made this place so beautiful
I'd never be able to leave.

1450
01:45:03,505 --> 01:45:05,798
Been dying to get rid of you.

1451
01:45:07,092 --> 01:45:09,010
This is my house.

1452
01:45:09,761 --> 01:45:13,514
I was born in that room.
So you were.

1453
01:45:14,641 --> 01:45:16,642
Welcome home.

1454
01:45:57,434 --> 01:45:58,893
Pap-pap me.

1455
01:45:59,644 --> 01:46:00,895
What?

1456
01:46:01,063 --> 01:46:03,522
Pap-pap me.